Bluetongue, Switzerland
-----------------------
Information received on [and dated] 03 Nov 2017 from Mr Hans Wyss, Chief Veterinary Officer, Schwarzenburgstrasse 161, Swiss Federal Veterinary Office, LIEBEFELD BERNE, Switzerland

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 19 Oct 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 23 Oct 2017
Report date: 03 Nov 2017
Date submitted to OIE: 03 Nov 2017
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: Mar 2010
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 8
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1 (BT_2017_1_BL): Bennwil, Bennwil, Waldenburg, BASEL-LANDSCHAFT
Date of start of the outbreak: 19 Oct 2017
Outbreak status: Resolved (03 Nov 2017)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Killed and disposed of/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 90/ 1/ 0/ 1/ 0

Outbreak 2 (BT_2017_1_JU): Saint-Ursanne, Saint-Ursanne, Porrentruy, JURA
Date of start of the outbreak: 23 Oct 2017
Outbreak status: Resolved (03 Nov 2017)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Killed and disposed of/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 58/ 1/ 0/ 1/ 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected
Species/ Susceptible/ Cases/ Deaths/ Killed and disposed of/ Slaughtered
Cattle/ 148/ 2/ 0/ 2/ 0
Outbreak statistics (rates apparent, in percentages)
Species/ morbidity rate/ mortality rate/ case fatality rate/ Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle/ 1.35/ 0.00/ 0.00/ 1.35/
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology: Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors
Epidemiological comments: All susceptible animals present on the 2 holdings were subject to individual sampling and blood was analysed for presence of virus and antibodies. All animals on the 2 holdings were negative for virus.

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; Stamping out [see comment]; Control of vectors; Vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); No treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: Zoning

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Institute of Virology and Immunology IVI (National laboratory)
Species/ Test/ Test date/ Result/
Cattle/ polymerase chain reaction (PCR)/ 23 Oct 2017/ Positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above]

